                    "company": "Plastic Soup Foundation",
                    "description": "Together with Waternet and The Great Bubble Barrier, and commissioned by the City of Amsterdam and Waterschap Amstel, Gooi and Vecht, we have measured what type of plastic waste and how much of it is captured by the Bubble Barrier at the Westerdok in Amsterdam. A group of volunteers helped us separate, count and weigh individual litter categories in accordance with the OSPAR method. This way we were able to determine what kind of waste and how much of it ends up in our beautiful canals.\nThis project ran from September 2021 until October 2022, and we hope to present the results in early 2023.",
